<p>When try to return object of type decimal using <code>Command.ExecuteScalar()</code> and use the "returned object" <code>.Tostring()</code> a trailing zero appears to the value</p>  <p>ex.</p>  <pre><code>dbCmd.CommandText = "select .12345 from dual" ;  object returnValue = dbCmd.ExecuteScalar();  string expectedValue =  returnValue.ToString(); </code></pre>  <blockquote>   <p>The expected result : .12345</p>      <p>The actual result  : .123450</p> </blockquote>  <p>I notice that trailing zero added only if the "the number of digits after the decimal point" is odd  ex.     if the command text is "select .123456 from dual" ;</p>  <blockquote>   <p>The expected result : .123456</p>      <p>The actual result  : .123456</p> </blockquote>